1
00:00:01,301 --> 00:00:03,069
( Waves crashing )

2
00:00:05,672 --> 00:00:09,543
Phinks: Right.
So where are we on the island?

3
00:00:09,576 --> 00:00:12,813
Let’s steal an accompany card
so we can go somewhere.

4
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:13,947
( Gasps )

5
00:00:18,619 --> 00:00:20,621
Man: Uninvited guests, huh?

6
00:00:22,656 --> 00:00:23,624
( Spiders grunt )

7
00:00:23,657 --> 00:00:24,625
Man: Hmm.

8
00:00:24,658 --> 00:00:27,027
Makes me nervous.

9
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,695
Just to be sure,

10
00:00:28,729 --> 00:00:31,632
you folks aren’t castaways,
are you?

11
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:34,902
I doubt it, since the strong
currents around the island

12
00:00:34,935 --> 00:00:37,938
make it virtually impossible
to drift here by accident.

13
00:00:38,972 --> 00:00:40,740
Phinks: This guy’s tough.

14
00:00:41,775 --> 00:00:43,377
Who the hell are you?

15
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:45,746
You supposed to be
our guide or something?

16
00:00:45,779 --> 00:00:49,316
Man: No, i’m just one
of the creators of this game.

17
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:50,851
You can call me razor.

18
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:53,687
I mainly handle
the emissive systems,

19
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,889
like, uh, traveling by spell

20
00:00:55,923 --> 00:00:58,692
- and trespassers.
- ( Spiders gasp )

21
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:03,096
Razor: This spell can only
be used by a gamemaster.

22
00:01:03,130 --> 00:01:05,499
Sorry, but you’ll have to leave.

23
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:08,335
Come back the right way,

24
00:01:08,368 --> 00:01:09,870
and you’ll be welcome here.

25
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:12,072
There’s an excellent item
in the game

26
00:01:12,105 --> 00:01:14,007
that you can obtain
by fighting me,

27
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:16,010
so if you decide to play,

28
00:01:16,043 --> 00:01:18,112
we’ll probably
get to fight eventually.

29
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:19,546
Phinks: Fine, then.

30
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:20,915
We’ll be right back

31
00:01:20,948 --> 00:01:22,917
through the front door
next time.

32
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:25,519
Razor: Eliminate on.

33
00:01:28,555 --> 00:01:31,892
Huh. That’s one
intimidating group of people.

34
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:34,127
I can tell you that. Hmm?

35
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:42,802
( Grunts )

36
00:01:49,142 --> 00:01:50,110
♪

37
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:52,012
( Singing in Japanese )

38
00:02:34,054 --> 00:02:36,056
♪

39
00:02:40,861 --> 00:02:44,098
Narrator: As gon continues
to train, he discovers a hint

40
00:02:44,131 --> 00:02:46,667
to developing
his ultimate technique.

41
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:49,469
Gon: Show me rock! Come on!

42
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:52,673
Jan Ken rock!

43
00:02:57,711 --> 00:02:59,213
Killua: Whoa!

44
00:02:59,246 --> 00:03:00,614
Bisky: I see.

45
00:03:00,647 --> 00:03:02,082
Gon: Next up!

46
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:03,650
All right.

47
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:04,885
Show me rock.

48
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:07,954
Jan Ken paper!

49
00:03:07,988 --> 00:03:09,523
- ( Boing )
- ( Music stops )

50
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:13,194
Bisky, how do I make my nen fly?

51
00:03:13,227 --> 00:03:14,195
( Killua groans )

52
00:03:14,228 --> 00:03:15,730
Bisky: Train more.

53
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:17,597
Killua: Paper’s
an emitter technique?

54
00:03:17,631 --> 00:03:18,899
Gon: Uh-huh.

55
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,901
And scissors is a transmuter.

56
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:24,204
Pretty soon, I want to try
to cut through a rock.

57
00:03:24,238 --> 00:03:25,673
Bisky: Understood.

58
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:27,808
That’s a reasonable
fighting technique.

59
00:03:27,841 --> 00:03:30,210
But a childish idea.

60
00:03:30,244 --> 00:03:32,613
Gon: I can focus my nen
in my fist,

61
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:35,015
but you know
how it takes a lot of time?

62
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,550
I was trying to figure out

63
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,718
a good way
that I could spend that time.

64
00:03:38,752 --> 00:03:42,256
When you were talking
about the game, it just hit me,

65
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:44,124
’cause I like that game.

66
00:03:44,157 --> 00:03:47,160
Bisky: Hmph. It’s important
to trust in your instincts.

67
00:03:47,194 --> 00:03:49,630
Those gut feelings
play a big role

68
00:03:49,663 --> 00:03:52,533
in techniques that require
multiple categories.

69
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:55,803
The real key is that it
should feel right to you.

70
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:57,738
- Killua: Uh, ahem.
- Bisky: Hmm?

71
00:03:57,771 --> 00:03:59,740
Gon: Hmm?

72
00:04:03,143 --> 00:04:04,678
( Both gasp )

73
00:04:04,711 --> 00:04:08,081
Killua: Well, this is
all i’ve got right now,

74
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:11,085
but if I charge it up,
it’s pretty strong.

75
00:04:11,118 --> 00:04:12,753
Gon: That’s awesome, killua!

76
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:14,521
You’re like an electric eel!

77
00:04:14,555 --> 00:04:16,090
Killua: Awful analogy.

78
00:04:16,123 --> 00:04:17,825
- Come on, man.
- Gon: What?

79
00:04:17,858 --> 00:04:21,095
Bisky: He can change aura
into electricity at his age?

80
00:04:21,128 --> 00:04:22,796
It’s frightening,

81
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:26,100
not to mention tragic.

82
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:28,836
His childhood must have
been a living hell.

83
00:04:28,869 --> 00:04:32,840
In fact, it’s a miracle that he
can smile at all anymore.

84
00:04:32,873 --> 00:04:34,875
♪

85
00:04:37,578 --> 00:04:39,113
Mm, look at them.

86
00:04:39,146 --> 00:04:43,317
They make such a great team.

87
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,953
Hmm. Well, what do you say?

88
00:04:45,986 --> 00:04:47,321
Shall we call it a day?

89
00:04:47,354 --> 00:04:48,322
Killua: Huh?

90
00:04:48,355 --> 00:04:49,890
Bisky: It’s a bit early,

91
00:04:49,923 --> 00:04:52,025
- but how ’bout a party?
- Killua: Party?

92
00:04:52,059 --> 00:04:55,129
Bisky: What do you boys do
to celebrate back home?

93
00:04:55,162 --> 00:04:57,765
- Gon: Celebrate?
- ( Bisky giggles )

94
00:04:57,798 --> 00:05:00,567
It’s almost new year’s
in the real world, isn’t it?

95
00:05:00,601 --> 00:05:04,238
Time flows at the same speed
in here as it does outside.

96
00:05:04,271 --> 00:05:06,640
- ( Gon gasps ) Oh, no!
- Killua: Hmm?

97
00:05:06,673 --> 00:05:10,243
Gon: I forgot! The deadline
for the hunter exam’s coming up!

98
00:05:10,277 --> 00:05:12,579
Killua: Oh, man.
And right when training

99
00:05:12,613 --> 00:05:14,849
was starting to get
kind of fun, too.

100
00:05:14,882 --> 00:05:18,185
Bisky: If my memory serves,
you have to apply by year’s end.

101
00:05:18,218 --> 00:05:19,953
Gon: Then we need to hurry!

102
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:22,089
But remind me
how we get outside again.

103
00:05:22,122 --> 00:05:23,824
Killua: I’m guessing
there are spell cards

104
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:25,592
to leave the game, right?

105
00:05:25,626 --> 00:05:29,096
Bisky: There are, so let’s take
another trip to masadora.

106
00:05:29,129 --> 00:05:30,731
Boys: All right!

107
00:05:32,132 --> 00:05:35,202
Bisky: Now let’s find
a place to have some tea.

108
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:37,671
Gon: We can’t.
We don’t have much time.

109
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:40,307
Killua: We can ask
at the stores we go to.

110
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:43,310
Shopkeeper: You want
to leave the island?

111
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:46,012
No sweat.
That’ll be 3,000 Jenny.

112
00:05:46,046 --> 00:05:48,315
- ( Killua groans )
- ( Gon grunts )

113
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:51,251
Shopkeeper: If you go
about 50 kilometers west,

114
00:05:51,285 --> 00:05:53,654
you’ll reach
the island’s only port.

115
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:56,723
You’ll have to defeat
or bribe the harbor master.

116
00:05:56,757 --> 00:06:00,327
If you do, you’ll get a ticket
that’ll transport you outside.

117
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,729
Gon: How big of a bribe
do you think?

118
00:06:02,763 --> 00:06:04,798
Shopkeeper: That depends
on how he’s feeling.

119
00:06:04,832 --> 00:06:05,933
Killua: Yeah, okay.

120
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:07,134
Shopkeeper: Your other option

121
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:09,269
is to use a leave spell card,

122
00:06:09,303 --> 00:06:11,739
but that one
is pretty rare, so...

123
00:06:11,772 --> 00:06:13,007
Gon: What do we do?

124
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,008
Killua: Head to the port.

125
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,643
Since its a rare card,

126
00:06:15,676 --> 00:06:18,913
it might not even show up,
no matter how much we spend.

127
00:06:18,946 --> 00:06:20,114
Gon: Yeah, you’re right.

128
00:06:20,147 --> 00:06:22,883
( Seabirds calling )

129
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:24,217
( Electricity crackles )

130
00:06:24,251 --> 00:06:26,286
( Glass shatters )

131
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,156
Both: Hmm?

132
00:06:29,189 --> 00:06:30,957
Killua: Voila.

133
00:06:30,991 --> 00:06:33,727
Killua: Heh. Well,
I guess now i’ll go ace the exam

134
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,894
and come right back.

135
00:06:34,928 --> 00:06:36,963
Gon: First go
to the lone cedar tree

136
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:38,699
that’s down by dolle harbor.

137
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,667
Magical beasts called kiriko
live there.

138
00:06:40,701 --> 00:06:42,169
Just tell them
that you’re my friend,

139
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:44,271
and they’ll take you
right to the exam site.

140
00:06:44,304 --> 00:06:46,406
Killua: Will do. See ya.

141
00:06:48,008 --> 00:06:50,010
♪

142
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:52,246
Bisky: All right, then.

143
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:54,248
Let’s get back to your training.

144
00:06:54,281 --> 00:06:55,883
Gon: Osu!

145
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:08,329
Woman: Welcome, sir.

146
00:07:08,362 --> 00:07:11,332
Killua, thinking:
Is this where I started?

147
00:07:11,365 --> 00:07:13,167
No, it’s not.

148
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,936
The girl looks familiar, though.

149
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:18,738
But that’s pretty typical
for games.

150
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:21,074
Woman: Will you be leaving
the island now?

151
00:07:21,108 --> 00:07:24,144
If so, please specify
your location.

152
00:07:24,178 --> 00:07:26,147
Killua: Do you have
dolle harbor?

153
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,415
Woman: Yes, I do.

154
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,349
Killua: Then just send me there.

155
00:07:29,383 --> 00:07:31,051
Woman: I understand.

156
00:07:32,085 --> 00:07:33,720
When you leave this island,

157
00:07:33,754 --> 00:07:36,390
all of the cards
that are in your free slots

158
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:38,926
will be deleted instantly.
Do you accept that?

159
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,761
Killua: Yeah, that’s fine.

160
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:42,296
Woman: Well, in that case,

161
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:45,766
we will be patiently awaiting
your return, sir.

162
00:07:50,237 --> 00:07:53,474
Killua: Guess i’m back
in the real world now, huh?

163
00:07:53,507 --> 00:07:55,175
Doesn’t feel any different.

164
00:07:56,443 --> 00:07:57,911
And book.

165
00:07:58,912 --> 00:08:00,714
So it doesn’t work out here.

166
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:01,815
Gotcha.

167
00:08:03,851 --> 00:08:07,421
I’ll submit my application
and head for that cedar tree.

168
00:08:07,454 --> 00:08:10,824
But first i’ve
gotta shower and change.

169
00:08:10,858 --> 00:08:12,259
Bisky: Okay.

170
00:08:12,292 --> 00:08:14,427
We’ll train
the whole time you’re running.

171
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:17,097
When you can form
numbers zero through nine,

172
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:19,065
all within one minute, you pass.

173
00:08:19,099 --> 00:08:20,767
( Gon grunting )

174
00:08:20,801 --> 00:08:22,436
Bisky: Huh?

175
00:08:22,469 --> 00:08:24,237
Gon: That hurt!

176
00:08:24,271 --> 00:08:25,439
( Groans )

177
00:08:25,472 --> 00:08:27,407
Bisky: What in the world
are you doing?!

178
00:08:27,441 --> 00:08:28,442
- ( Whooshing )
- Huh?

179
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,415
Aren’t you...

180
00:08:34,448 --> 00:08:37,851
Player: I can see that your
other friend isn’t with you.

181
00:08:37,885 --> 00:08:40,020
Bisky: What’s that thing
on your shoulder?

182
00:08:40,053 --> 00:08:42,255
What happened to you?
Is something wrong?

183
00:08:42,289 --> 00:08:43,257
( Timer beeping )

184
00:08:43,290 --> 00:08:44,992
Player: The bomber got us.

185
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:45,993
Hear me out.

186
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,561
I have something to say.

187
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:52,132
( Birds squawk )

188
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:54,168
Bisky: So he was the bomber.

189
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:56,837
Player: The others
are back in our hideout

190
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:59,406
waiting for him
to disarm the bombs.

191
00:08:59,439 --> 00:09:02,142
They believe
in the terms he gave them,

192
00:09:02,176 --> 00:09:03,978
but i’m not as convinced.

193
00:09:04,011 --> 00:09:06,146
Gon: Now what? What can we do?

194
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:08,416
Bisky: If they’re prepared
to accept casualties--

195
00:09:08,448 --> 00:09:09,983
- player: Won’t happen.
- ( Both gasp )

196
00:09:10,017 --> 00:09:12,520
Player: The very first ones
to jump him

197
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:15,256
will be the first ones
to be sacrificed.

198
00:09:15,289 --> 00:09:17,825
Who would
ever volunteer for that?

199
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:19,393
Gon: Good point.

200
00:09:19,426 --> 00:09:22,863
Player: Jispa was the most
proficient of us in combat,

201
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:25,198
yet he was beaten instantly.

202
00:09:25,232 --> 00:09:28,268
We were already doomed
at that point.

203
00:09:28,302 --> 00:09:30,938
And allowing genthru
to leave the game

204
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:32,406
proved to be a fatal mistake.

205
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,075
We foolishly began to celebrate

206
00:09:35,108 --> 00:09:37,344
before we had
the chance to verify

207
00:09:37,377 --> 00:09:40,046
each member’s cards
and assigned roles,

208
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:43,050
and that was when
he caught us off guard.

209
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:45,452
I hate to say it,

210
00:09:45,485 --> 00:09:48,188
but i--i was so distracted

211
00:09:48,222 --> 00:09:52,460
that I simply didn’t see him
use leave until it was too late.

212
00:09:52,493 --> 00:09:55,329
Bisky: You were probably
focused on his explanation,

213
00:09:55,362 --> 00:09:57,364
trying to figure out
its meaning.

214
00:09:57,397 --> 00:10:00,433
Player: Yeah. We were
thrust into that situation

215
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:02,469
with absolutely
no warning at all.

216
00:10:02,503 --> 00:10:06,207
Of course, we were all
too stunned to take any action.

217
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:10,177
Bisky: I see, but may I ask why
you’re telling us all this?

218
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:11,878
♪

219
00:10:11,912 --> 00:10:14,181
Player: Out of everyone
i’ve met here on the island,

220
00:10:14,214 --> 00:10:16,583
I believe you’re the ones
I can rely on the most.

221
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:20,087
If you communicate
with any other players,

222
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,423
I beg you to tell them all
about the bomber.

223
00:10:23,457 --> 00:10:27,194
If they know about his ability,
they can guard against it.

224
00:10:27,227 --> 00:10:31,998
And if it comes down to it,
I want you to try to avenge us.

225
00:10:32,032 --> 00:10:35,302
At the very least,
do not let him clear the game.

226
00:10:37,104 --> 00:10:38,238
( Gon grunts )

227
00:10:38,272 --> 00:10:39,406
Bisky: We understand.

228
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:40,640
Player: Thank you.

229
00:10:42,643 --> 00:10:45,346
I’ll use what little time
I have left

230
00:10:45,379 --> 00:10:48,582
to tell as many as I can
about the bomber.

231
00:10:48,615 --> 00:10:50,217
Book.

232
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,384
Return on!

233
00:10:51,418 --> 00:10:52,519
Bunzen!

234
00:10:56,356 --> 00:10:58,458
( Whooshing )

235
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:03,563
Actually,
the truth of the matter

236
00:11:03,597 --> 00:11:06,033
is that when I used
magnetic force,

237
00:11:06,066 --> 00:11:08,735
those two were
the only players I could find.

238
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:12,206
But flattery works wonders.

239
00:11:12,239 --> 00:11:14,975
When it comes
to deactivating someone’s nen,

240
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,477
every thousandth
of a percent counts.

241
00:11:18,478 --> 00:11:20,146
Now, then...

242
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:23,684
Nickes has probably gone off
to meet with the bombers.

243
00:11:23,717 --> 00:11:26,253
However, if what they promised

244
00:11:26,286 --> 00:11:29,656
turns out to be
a mass detonation...

245
00:11:31,258 --> 00:11:32,459
Better get started.

246
00:11:40,501 --> 00:11:43,070
Genthru: You’re finally here.

247
00:11:43,103 --> 00:11:45,472
Now hand over your ring.

248
00:11:45,506 --> 00:11:48,275
Nickes: Jispa has passed away.

249
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:49,442
Genthru: That’s nice.

250
00:11:49,476 --> 00:11:51,278
- Your ring?
- ( Nickes sputters )

251
00:11:51,311 --> 00:11:53,480
Disarm everyone’s bombs first!

252
00:11:53,514 --> 00:11:55,483
Genthru: Hell, no.

253
00:11:55,516 --> 00:11:58,486
First I have to take that ring
back inside the game,

254
00:11:58,519 --> 00:12:01,288
and once I do,
i’ll confirm that all the cards

255
00:12:01,321 --> 00:12:02,489
are indeed in the binder.

256
00:12:03,524 --> 00:12:06,093
Then i’ll disarm the bombs.

257
00:12:06,126 --> 00:12:08,495
This is the last time.

258
00:12:08,529 --> 00:12:11,098
Hand over the ring.

259
00:12:11,131 --> 00:12:12,299
♪

260
00:12:12,332 --> 00:12:14,100
( Nickes groans )

261
00:12:17,137 --> 00:12:20,107
Genthru: Sub, go ahead,
and put it on.

262
00:12:21,141 --> 00:12:23,110
If you put on a second ring

263
00:12:23,143 --> 00:12:24,544
when you’re outside the game,

264
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:26,480
your original data
gets overwritten.

265
00:12:26,513 --> 00:12:27,514
Sub: Mm-hmm.

266
00:12:27,548 --> 00:12:28,716
Genthru: Now then,

267
00:12:28,749 --> 00:12:31,151
let’s head back inside together.

268
00:12:31,185 --> 00:12:32,386
Hold on.

269
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:34,121
What’s your name again?

270
00:12:34,154 --> 00:12:36,523
( Nickes growls )

271
00:12:41,562 --> 00:12:42,663
( Chorus vocalizing )

272
00:12:42,696 --> 00:12:44,698
( Player speaking
foreign language )

273
00:12:47,568 --> 00:12:49,570
Spirits of the forest,

274
00:12:49,603 --> 00:12:53,540
remove the unclean nen
that is now possessing my body.

275
00:13:00,514 --> 00:13:04,518
Now, what will it be, I wonder.

276
00:13:08,388 --> 00:13:11,424
I call upon the power
of the forest spirits

277
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:15,162
and combine it with my own
to create a nen beast

278
00:13:15,195 --> 00:13:18,165
capable of consuming
the nen abilities of others.

279
00:13:19,199 --> 00:13:21,168
( Beast growling )

280
00:13:21,201 --> 00:13:22,836
Player: It’s a big one.

281
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:27,842
As I feared, the bomber’s
countdown is a powerful nen.

282
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,678
Player #2: So how’d it go?

283
00:13:31,712 --> 00:13:33,380
Player #3: Did he
disarm them yet?

284
00:13:34,414 --> 00:13:35,682
Sub: Now book.

285
00:13:38,185 --> 00:13:39,386
Genthru: Okay.

286
00:13:39,419 --> 00:13:42,689
81 specified-slot card types.

287
00:13:42,723 --> 00:13:44,124
They’re here, all right.

288
00:13:44,158 --> 00:13:46,394
Nickes: Look, we did
everything you wanted,

289
00:13:46,426 --> 00:13:48,595
so now disarm all the bombs!

290
00:13:48,629 --> 00:13:50,131
Genthru: But of course.

291
00:13:50,164 --> 00:13:51,632
I’m a man of my word.

292
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:55,135
But first, you need
to hand over three leave cards.

293
00:13:55,169 --> 00:13:56,604
( Nickes gasps )

294
00:13:56,637 --> 00:13:58,205
♪

295
00:13:58,238 --> 00:13:59,372
Genthru: Okay, then.

296
00:13:59,406 --> 00:14:01,375
Looks like we have a deal.

297
00:14:01,408 --> 00:14:02,609
Sub, bara.

298
00:14:03,644 --> 00:14:06,413
( Beast grumbling )

299
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:24,264
( Players gasping )

300
00:14:25,265 --> 00:14:26,433
Genthru: Here goes.

301
00:14:30,671 --> 00:14:31,906
Bombers: Release!

302
00:14:31,939 --> 00:14:33,774
( Players sigh )

303
00:14:33,807 --> 00:14:35,676
( Screaming )

304
00:14:35,709 --> 00:14:37,377
♪

305
00:14:50,757 --> 00:14:53,326
( Genthru laughs )

306
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:56,163
I just released all of you...

307
00:14:56,196 --> 00:14:58,331
From your fear.

308
00:14:58,365 --> 00:15:00,601
( Bombers laugh )

309
00:15:00,634 --> 00:15:01,735
( Nickes gasps ) That...

310
00:15:01,768 --> 00:15:04,437
Wasn’t our deal.

311
00:15:04,471 --> 00:15:05,572
Genthru: Hmm?

312
00:15:05,606 --> 00:15:07,608
You’re all losers,

313
00:15:07,641 --> 00:15:10,844
and I don’t keep promises
to losers.

314
00:15:10,878 --> 00:15:12,913
"Release" doesn’t disarm.

315
00:15:12,946 --> 00:15:14,848
It’s the trigger word.

316
00:15:14,882 --> 00:15:17,451
( Bombers laughing )

317
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:21,254
Leave on!

318
00:15:22,823 --> 00:15:24,525
( Player #1 sighs )

319
00:15:24,558 --> 00:15:27,661
At least now I don’t have
to worry about exploding.

320
00:15:27,694 --> 00:15:29,396
- ( Beast grumbling )
- Player #1: Huh?

321
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:32,365
But i’m stuck with this guy

322
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:35,903
until genthru
reverses his ability or dies.

323
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:42,510
I’ve got myself
a troublesome companion.

324
00:15:46,346 --> 00:15:47,881
Hey, be still.

325
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:52,319
The bomber’s
going to kill us all.

326
00:15:52,352 --> 00:15:54,221
He’ll assume he succeeded.

327
00:15:54,254 --> 00:15:57,324
I’ll use it to my advantage.

328
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:01,361
( Bird squawks )

329
00:16:04,498 --> 00:16:05,532
Gon: Bisky?

330
00:16:05,566 --> 00:16:07,735
Bisky: Hmm?

331
00:16:07,768 --> 00:16:12,239
Gon: I think we should go
drop by their hideout real fast.

332
00:16:12,272 --> 00:16:14,674
Bisky: Time’s probably
already up for them.

333
00:16:14,708 --> 00:16:18,345
Besides, he didn’t even
tell us where it is.

334
00:16:18,378 --> 00:16:19,880
And even if we could find it,

335
00:16:19,913 --> 00:16:22,716
we’d still need a spell card
that could take us there,

336
00:16:22,749 --> 00:16:24,351
and we simply don’t have one.

337
00:16:24,384 --> 00:16:26,019
Gon: I know,

338
00:16:26,053 --> 00:16:29,023
but some of them could have
survived the explosion.

339
00:16:29,056 --> 00:16:30,024
It’s possible.

340
00:16:30,057 --> 00:16:31,358
Bisky: But doubtful.

341
00:16:31,391 --> 00:16:33,260
If the bomber’s powerful enough

342
00:16:33,293 --> 00:16:36,263
to place bombs on his targets
without them noticing,

343
00:16:36,296 --> 00:16:38,365
he’d never be that careless.

344
00:16:38,398 --> 00:16:40,767
- ( Gon sighs )
- Bisky: However...

345
00:16:40,801 --> 00:16:42,836
If we just continue
to play the game,

346
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:45,506
then we’re bound to run into
the bomber at some point.

347
00:16:45,539 --> 00:16:46,974
And given that fact,

348
00:16:47,007 --> 00:16:50,577
then sooner or later, we may
need to visit their hideout.

349
00:16:50,611 --> 00:16:51,979
( Gon grunts )

350
00:16:52,012 --> 00:16:54,014
Bisky: But we
still need spell cards.

351
00:16:54,047 --> 00:16:57,584
Let’s go to masadora and sell
our monster cards to buy some.

352
00:16:57,618 --> 00:16:58,986
Gon: Yeah! ( Laughs )

353
00:17:02,623 --> 00:17:04,959
Hey, bisky,
how long do you think

354
00:17:04,992 --> 00:17:07,595
it’ll take me
to master my signature move?

355
00:17:07,628 --> 00:17:10,531
Bisky: Well, you are just
starting to develop your nen.

356
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:13,400
Hard to say when
your power and speed will peak.

357
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:14,401
Gon: It is?

358
00:17:14,434 --> 00:17:15,635
Bisky: That said,

359
00:17:15,669 --> 00:17:17,571
i’d be more than
a little bit surprised

360
00:17:17,604 --> 00:17:20,307
if it took you very long
to get the form down.

361
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:22,342
Gon: Really? How long?

362
00:17:22,376 --> 00:17:26,313
Bisky: Let me see. Hmm.

363
00:17:26,346 --> 00:17:29,716
You may have it ready
by the time killua’s back.

364
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,318
( Gon grunts )

365
00:17:31,351 --> 00:17:32,853
All right!

366
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:36,089
I can’t wait to see the look
on his face when he sees it.

367
00:17:36,123 --> 00:17:38,125
♪

368
00:17:41,361 --> 00:17:43,430
Shopkeeper:
You two are so lucky.

369
00:17:43,463 --> 00:17:44,798
We just recently received

370
00:17:44,832 --> 00:17:47,335
a huge shipment
of different spell cards.

371
00:17:47,367 --> 00:17:50,370
Gon: So these are the ones
they’ve been hoarding.

372
00:17:53,774 --> 00:17:55,442
We bought 60 between us,

373
00:17:55,475 --> 00:17:57,944
so there are all kinds
of types here.

374
00:17:57,978 --> 00:17:59,346
( Bisky gasps )

375
00:17:59,379 --> 00:18:00,447
Gon, look.

376
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:01,948
Gon: Hmm? ( Gasps )

377
00:18:01,982 --> 00:18:03,517
An s-rank!

378
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:04,785
There are only 10

379
00:18:04,818 --> 00:18:05,952
in the whole game.

380
00:18:05,986 --> 00:18:07,354
Bisky: What do you think?

381
00:18:07,387 --> 00:18:09,556
Save it, or should we
use it right now?

382
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:12,726
Gon: Hey, don’t ask me!
I don’t know what to do!

383
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:13,893
Bisky: Shh. Be quiet.

384
00:18:13,927 --> 00:18:15,762
Do you want people
getting suspicious?

385
00:18:15,796 --> 00:18:17,531
( Gon groans )

386
00:18:17,564 --> 00:18:21,068
If only killua was still here.

387
00:18:21,101 --> 00:18:23,370
( Killua sneezes )

388
00:18:23,403 --> 00:18:24,704
( Sighs )

389
00:18:24,738 --> 00:18:26,840
( Kiriko father sniffing )

390
00:18:26,874 --> 00:18:29,744
Well, you certainly do
smell like gon.

391
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:31,778
Kiriko mother: I miss that kid.

392
00:18:33,814 --> 00:18:35,716
Kiriko father: We’ll take you
to the exam site.

393
00:18:35,749 --> 00:18:37,117
Just leave it to us.

394
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:39,786
Killua: Let’s hurry.
I need to ace it

395
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:42,456
and then hurry back to gon
right away.

396
00:18:42,489 --> 00:18:44,391
Kiriko mother:
Sure, but the exam

397
00:18:44,424 --> 00:18:46,660
won’t officially start
for a few days.

398
00:18:46,693 --> 00:18:48,395
Killua: Oh, yeah, that’s right.

399
00:18:48,428 --> 00:18:49,963
Kiriko mother: In the meantime,

400
00:18:49,997 --> 00:18:52,766
why don’t you tell us all
about your adventures with gon?

401
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:55,402
Killua: Okay. Well,
there was that one time

402
00:18:55,435 --> 00:18:57,437
that he came to my house.

403
00:18:57,471 --> 00:18:59,473
♪

404
00:19:07,848 --> 00:19:09,817
Gon: Hah!

405
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:11,952
Bisky: You’re making
steady progress, gon.

406
00:19:11,985 --> 00:19:14,888
You’re right on track to have
your ultimate technique ready.

407
00:19:14,922 --> 00:19:18,526
Gon: It helps that this is
such a safe place to practice.

408
00:19:18,559 --> 00:19:20,694
With this view,
we can spot anyone

409
00:19:20,727 --> 00:19:23,830
before they get close enough
to use an attack spell.

410
00:19:23,864 --> 00:19:26,467
People are watching
from masadora.

411
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:30,738
I feel it like I felt people
watching us at the start point.

412
00:19:30,771 --> 00:19:33,741
But this time, we’ve got
plenty of attack spells.

413
00:19:33,774 --> 00:19:34,742
Bisky: Hmm.

414
00:19:34,775 --> 00:19:36,744
Yes, but just to be safe,

415
00:19:36,777 --> 00:19:39,947
I already cast
a blackout curtain card.

416
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:41,615
- Gon: Mm.
- Bisky: Still...

417
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:44,618
There’s no real point
in worrying about spell cards.

418
00:19:44,651 --> 00:19:47,454
You just focus
on training your hardest.

419
00:19:47,487 --> 00:19:48,955
Gon: Osu!

420
00:19:48,989 --> 00:19:50,991
♪

421
00:19:55,596 --> 00:19:58,532
Bisky: Right.
It’s been a minute.

422
00:19:58,565 --> 00:19:59,566
Next.

423
00:20:06,206 --> 00:20:07,574
( Gon gasps )

424
00:20:07,608 --> 00:20:10,144
Aw, man,
it didn’t reach far enough.

425
00:20:10,177 --> 00:20:13,147
Bisky: Don’t worry. You’re
definitely in far better shape

426
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:14,982
than a transmuter would be.

427
00:20:15,015 --> 00:20:16,250
Be patient.

428
00:20:16,283 --> 00:20:18,519
Focus on maintaining
the shape of your aura.

429
00:20:18,552 --> 00:20:21,221
If you can do it
for an extended period of time,

430
00:20:21,255 --> 00:20:22,990
- you’re all set.
- Gon: Osu!

431
00:20:23,023 --> 00:20:25,726
Bisky: The longer
you can maintain that sphere,

432
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:27,628
the stronger your ten is.

433
00:20:27,661 --> 00:20:29,796
And once you’ve
trained long enough

434
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:31,699
and put in some real effort,

435
00:20:31,732 --> 00:20:33,734
you’ll be able to maintain
an aura sphere

436
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:36,003
for two or three days
at a time.

437
00:20:36,036 --> 00:20:38,939
You should get to where
you can reach that rock

438
00:20:38,972 --> 00:20:40,707
by the end of the day.

439
00:20:40,741 --> 00:20:41,742
( Gon grunts )

440
00:20:44,845 --> 00:20:45,813
- ( Crack )
- ( Gasps )

441
00:20:45,846 --> 00:20:47,548
You’re right! I got it!

442
00:20:47,581 --> 00:20:48,816
Bisky: That was quick.

443
00:20:48,849 --> 00:20:51,251
This proves
that he’s been working hard

444
00:20:51,285 --> 00:20:53,954
on his ten and ren every day.

445
00:20:53,987 --> 00:20:55,222
All right.

446
00:20:55,255 --> 00:20:57,591
Let’s go back
to practicing the basics.

447
00:20:58,692 --> 00:20:59,893
Gon: Osu!

448
00:20:59,927 --> 00:21:01,228
♪

449
00:21:01,261 --> 00:21:03,697
Narrator: Gon continues
to train with bisky

450
00:21:03,730 --> 00:21:06,199
to master
his signature technique.

451
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:08,669
Killua has temporarily
left the game

452
00:21:08,702 --> 00:21:10,204
to retake the hunter exam.

453
00:21:10,237 --> 00:21:13,107
The boys, each in their own way,

454
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:16,143
are working hard
to reach their goals.

455
00:21:16,176 --> 00:21:18,178
( Singing in Japanese )

